📝 Task Manager (Node.js + Express + EJS)

A simple Task Manager Web App built with Node.js, Express, and EJS.
This application allows users to create tasks, store them as .txt files, and view task details on a clean, TailwindCSS-powered UI.

🚀 Features

📂 Create new tasks with a title and description.

📝 Tasks are saved as .txt files inside the files/ directory.

🔍 View task details by clicking Read More.

🎨 Styled with TailwindCSS for a modern UI.

⚡ Built with Express.js and EJS templates.

🛠 Tech Stack

Backend: Node.js, Express.js

Frontend: EJS, TailwindCSS

Database: File System (stores tasks as .txt files)

📂 Project Structure
├── files/                # Stores task files (.txt)
│   ├── example.txt
├── views/                # EJS templates
│   ├── index.ejs         # Homepage (task listing + create form)
│   ├── show.ejs          # Task details page
├── public/               # Static assets (CSS, JS, images if any)
├── index.js              # Main server file
├── package.json          # Project dependencies

⚙️ Installation & Setup

Clone the repository

git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/<your-repo-name>.git
cd <your-repo-name>


Install dependencies

npm install


Start the server

node index.js


Open in browser

http://localhost:3000

